author: Frank Torres
title: Lena Juarez featured at Republicans in Action meeting
text:
Lena Juarez featured at Republicans in Action meeting October 11, 2015 Pinterest 0 
On Saturday Lena Juarez , President of the Government Affairs Firm JEJ & Associates , briefed the Republicans in Action Group of Seminole county to provide insight on this year’s legislative session and to provide a preview of what could happen in Tallahassee next year. 
Juarez is a Central Florida native, who went to Winter Park High School and first got involved in politics at a young age, campaigning for lawmakers like Lou Frey , Rich Crotty and Toni Jennings . After graduating from Florida State she was able to find opportunities in Government affairs that helped lead here to where she is today. 
She currently represents public and private clients in healthcare, education, and transportation. Reflecting on this year’s tumultuous legislative session she says “Not a lot got done. I know there is frustration from the lawmakers, lobbying corp, and the clients because they want to see things happen.” 
Juarez is hopeful that the leaders in the Senate and the House will be able to work together continuing “I’d really like to see both of them get their top priorities passed.” 
Despite the rise in technology, she knows face to face communication will always be the best way to get things done in the legislative process “It’ always is. Persistence Good communication, ethical representation, those will always the best way to get things done.” Lena Juarez, President JEJ & Associates Readers who read this, also read these
